# Treblo API key pool — one key per line.
#
# Rename this file to `.treblo-keys` and fill it with your Treblo account keys
# (one Treblo account per line). Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are
# ignored, so you may group/annotate your accounts:
#
#   # ---- batch 1 ----
#   sksonauto_aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa
#   sksonauto_bbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb
#   # ---- batch 2 ----
#   sksonauto_cccccccccccccccccccccccccccccccc
#
# Then point the backend at it:
#
#   TREBLO_KEYS_FILE=.treblo-keys      (in backend/.env)
#
# The backend dedupes and loads every key here into the multi-key failover
# pool. When a generation fails on one key (out of credits, 401, 5xx, timeout),
# the next key is tried automatically (see src/providers/keys.js).
#
# IMPORTANT: never commit the real `.treblo-keys` file. It is git-ignored.
